title: Identifying a list of fonts?
content:
I need some help identifying a set of fonts that's been given to me.. I've tried everything, but the only thing I've found is the 2nd one, le mons... Any help on any of them would be greatly appreciated :)

| Attachment | Size |
| --- | --- |
| [Picture1.jpg](http://web.archive.org/web/20140828234926/http:/typophile.com/files/Picture1_6.jpg) | 168.03 KB |
| [Picture2.jpg](http://web.archive.org/web/20140828234926/http:/typophile.com/files/Picture2_1.jpg) | 175.48 KB |
author: TheMentalGoose

comments.content:
Pic1 No1 looks like someone has made an outline version of [Castellar](http://web.archive.org/web/20140828234926/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/adobe/castellar/).  
Don

No8 looks like someone has made an outline version of [Princetown](http://web.archive.org/web/20140828234926/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/letraset/princetown/).  
Don

My mind is wired to recognize fonts as black-on-white. Lots of "I should know this'un"s but this outlining is doing me in!

#2 must be [Impact](http://web.archive.org/web/20140828234926/http:/www.microsoft.com/typography/fonts/font.aspx?FMID=32).
